NOTES: This Amazilia was in the vicinity of two Piranga roseogularis (recorded in LNS 103307) and one Dendroica magnolia (recorded in LNS 103309).  The final call in this recording (LNS 103308) is Dendroica magnolia, not Amazilia yucatanensis.

[These are the somewhat tinny, "tik" notes regularly given by this species in a variety of contexts.  The notes are given here both singly and in short series.  Quality added (1-2 - at least where calls of the Dendroica can be avoided) - CAM - 22 April 2005].

mediaNotes: Two cuts from a bird singing in flight in somewhat open mesquite woodland adjacent to taller growth. While singing the bird was flying horizontally between patches of mesquite trees, and I only heard this vocalization right around first light, when many birds were giving it.  The middle cut is of calls from the singing individual as it chased away another hummingbird.
